</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Brass screw, flat head. Cost about 20c, or package of 10 for $2.00{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2d/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2d/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Drill press. An inexpensive press is just fine for this project. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4e/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4e/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Spade bit, same size as base of the rain gauge. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a8/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a8/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Estimate the location of the centre and make a small mark. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e2/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e2/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Measure the distance from the mark to the edges of the puck. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Move the mark until all distances to the edge are the same. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7a/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7a/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If drawing lines on the puck, keep them in the central area so they will disappear when the hole is drilled in the puck. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5b/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5b/Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Hockey-Puck-Rain-Gauge-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
